Section: libs
Priority: required
Description: integrity-protected filesystem image library for ostree
 composefs is a Linux filesystem that mounts read-only OS images backed
 by a content-addressed store. Every file is verified at read time using
 fs-verity, making it impossible to tamper with the deployed OS tree at
 rest without detection.
 .
 Required by libostree when built with composefs support enabled, which
 is mandatory for bootc deployments with image integrity enforcement.
